      underside: "Pores, not gills: tubes 0.4-0.6 cm deep with adnate to decurrent attachment, yellow and staining reddish-brown when bruised; pores large (1-2 mm), angular, slightly wider than long (about 9-10 per cm radially, 12-13 per cm tangentially), darkening with age.",
      stem: "3-9 cm by 0.4-1 cm, roughly equal in width, often crooked, becoming hollow with age; lemon-yellow surface covered with glandular dots that bruise when handled. The partial veil is not attached to the stipe and usually leaves no ring.",
      fleshColor: "Mustard yellow, staining pinkish-brown when cut or bruised.",
      sporePrintColor: "Cinnamon-colored.",
