    toxicityNotes: "Nonpoisonous, but some susceptible individuals experience allergic contact dermatitis after touching it; symptoms generally develop one to two days after contact, persist about a week, then disappear without treatment. Cooking the fruit bodies inactivates the responsible allergens. The slimy caps and pore layer are typically removed before consumption.",
