      underside: "Pores, not gills: a layer of spongy yellow to yellow-brown angular pores up to 2.5 mm wide and radially arranged, with tubes 5-12 mm deep; pores range from yellow to brownish-yellow to ochre and stain brownish or reddish-brown when bruised, and are covered by a whitish partial veil in young specimens.",
      stem: "6-12 cm long and usually 1-3 cm thick, yellow, sometimes with reddish streaks (particularly below the ring zone), solid and yellow within; usually lacking the glandular dots characteristic of some Suillus species; either equal in width throughout or tapered downwards. The ring is delicate and floccose (woolly-tufted) and soon disappears or leaves a thin whitish ring.",
      fleshColor: "Thick and yellow, either unchanged when bruised or broken or turning pinkish-red; the stem-base tissue may weakly stain bluish-green when cut, though this is not usually apparent in mature specimens.",
